title: Ground News - A Palestinian woman displaced by the war in Gaza gives birth to quadruplets
text:
Summary by www.larazon.es Iman al-Masry had to leave behind her home in the city of Beit Hanoon, in the northwestern Gaza Strip, as a result of Israeli attacks in response to the Hamas attacks of October 7. The 28-year-old woman walked five kilometers with her three children to the Jabalia refugee camp in search of a means of transport to take them to Deir el-Balah, to the south of Gaza, where the fighting had not yet come.
